  "body": "Hi!\r\n\r\nIn our validator config, we have multiple beacon-chain endpoints configured through the **--beacon-rpc-gateway-provider**  and **--beacon-rpc-provider** flags. However, whenever there is some sort of disconnection between the validator and the connected beacon-chain, the node does not failover to the next beacon-chain in the configured list. Instead, it just hangs and does not try to reconnect to the original beacon-chain endpoint or a new one. When this happens, the beacon node being used would still be healthy however the connection to it may have had a hiccup, and the validator client stops sending requests to it.\r\n\r\nIn addition, we also see a spike in `grpc_method=\"DomainData\" DeadlineExceeded` errors around this time.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
